      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>This elegant tailored suit resembles a @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.oVY3IItOrAPiZoXz]{platinum AbadarCorp travel suit} and has the same statistics as that armor. In addition, sigils of divination woven into the fabric of the suit subtly alert you to lies. When wearing a suit of <em>boardroom attire</em>, roll twice when attempting @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.GMkLZsN3a7YPvA03.JournalEntryPage.nBrYkGfNBJAHe0xJ]{Sense Motive} checks to detect deception and use the higher result. In addition, you never think a truthful statement contains deceptions, even if you fail your check by 5 or more.</p>\n<p><em>Currently missing functionality to mark this item towards the Magicical Item&nbsp;</em><em>Worn</em><em>limit. Please create a magic item to represent this, with the&nbsp;</em><em>Magicical Item&nbsp;</em><em>Worn&nbsp;</em><em>limit checkbox on.</em></p>"
